# Chain Step 3 Is Not Well Posed On The Second Budget Because No Honest Two-Triad Shared-Mode Support Survives

Status: `INFERRED` current-budget obstruction verdict

On the Step-3 two-triad shared-mode budget, no honest finite exact support
remains available for Chain Step 3.

The branch's second-budget closure audit already kills the honest seed
families: the generic five-orbit shared-mode fan spills on the first honest
pass, and the four-orbit mirror / parallelogram subfamily also spills on the
first honest pass.

The only cosmetically tidy pictures left after that audit are over-pruned
pseudo-survivors.
Once their first forced orbit is restored and admissible enlargement is run on
the same ledger, both pictures spill again immediately.

So the sharp current-budget obstruction is:
recursive closure already spills on every honest two-triad shared-mode seed,
and the only tidy pseudo-survivors fail the required admissible-enlargement
audit once their first forced orbit is restored.

This is a second-budget verdict only.
It does not authorize mission-level termination, and it does not self-authorize
automatic escalation beyond a fresh controller review of the next rung.

