+# Connected Two-Triad Shared-Mode Seeds Reduce To A Generic Five-Orbit Family And A Four-Orbit Parallelogram Family
+
+Status: `INFERRED` Step-3 shared-mode seed catalog on the frozen equivalence
+sheet
+
+After quotienting by the frozen Step-1 and Step-2 equivalences
+`conjugation`,
+`triad relabeling`,
+and representative changes inside the same mirror-complete orbit, every
+connected two-triad cluster that shares one wavevector orbit with a first
+triad can be written in the canonical form
+
+`T(a,b,c) = { (a,b,a+b), (a,c,a+c) }`.
+
+On that frozen sheet, the honest second-budget geometric seed catalog has
+exactly two families.
+If the support has five distinct wavevector orbits up to conjugation, the
+cluster is the generic family
+`T_gen(a,b,c)`,
+with distinct representatives
+`a`,
+`b`,
+`c`,
+`a+b`,
+and
+`a+c`.
+If one additional coincidence collapses the support to four orbits, the
+cluster can be re-centered to the canonical mirror / parallelogram form
+`T_par(a,b) = { (a,b,a+b), (a,-b,a-b) }`.
+
+So re-centered drawings do not create extra second-budget families.
+Every genuine connected shared-mode seed at this rung belongs either to the
+generic five-orbit fan or to the four-orbit parallelogram subfamily.
+
+Filed from:
